Education Act of 1965 (20 U.S.C. 1002). 

(5)  QUALIFYING

EMERGENCY.The 

term 

qualifying  emergency  has  the  meaning  given  the 

term  in  section  3502  of  the  CARES  Act  (Public 

Law 116136), as amended by this Act. 

(6)  QUALIFYING EMERGENCY PERIOD.The 

term  qualifying  emergency  period  means  the  pe-

riod 

(A)  beginning  on  the  first  day  of  a  quali-

fying emergency; and 

(B)  ending  on  the  later  of  the  date  on 

which  the  qualifying  emergency  expires  or  June 

30, 2021. 

(7)  SECRETARY.The  term  Secretary  means 

the Secretary of Education. 

