Subtitle BFinancial Aid Access 

SEC.  121.  EMERGENCY  FINANCIAL  AID  GRANTS  EXCLUDED 

FROM NEED ANALYSIS. 

(a)  TREATMENT OF EMERGENCY FINANCIAL AID 

GRANTS FOR NEED ANALYSIS.Notwithstanding  any 

provision of the Higher Education Act of 1965 (20 U.S.C. 

1001 et seq.), emergency financial aid grants 

(1)  shall  not  be  included  as  income  or  assets 

(including  untaxed  income  and  benefits  under  sec-

tion  480(b)  of  the  Higher  Education  Act  of  1965 

(20  U.S.C.  1807vv(b)))  in  the  computation  of  ex-

pected  family  contribution  for  any  program  funded 

in  whole  or  in  part  under  the  Higher  Education  Act 

of 1965 (20 U.S.C. 1001 et seq.); and 

(2)  shall  not  be  treated  as  estimated  financial 

assistance  for  the  purposes  of  section  471  or  section 

480(j)  of  the  Higher  Education  Act  of  1965  (20 

U.S.C. 1087kk; 1087vv(j)). 

(b)  DEFINITION.In  this  section,  the  term  emer-

gency financial aid grant means 

