(e) DEFINITIONS.In this section: 

(1)  COVERED AWARD YEAR.The  term  cov-

ered award year means 

(A)  an  award  year  during  which  there  is  a 

qualifying emergency; and 

(B)  the  first  award  year  beginning  after 

the end of such qualifying emergency. 

(2)  MEANS-TESTED FEDERAL BENEFIT.The 

term  means-tested  Federal  benefit  includes  the 

following: 

(A)  The  supplemental  security  income  pro-

gram under title XVI of the Social Security Act 

(42 U.S.C. 1381 et seq.). 

(B)  The  supplemental  nutrition  assistance 

program  under  the  Food  and  Nutrition  Act  of 

2008 (7 U.S.C. 2011 et seq.). 

(C)  The  free  and  reduced  price  school 

lunch  program  established  under  the  Richard 

B.  Russell  National  School  Lunch  Act  (42 

U.S.C. 1751 et seq.). 

(D)  The  program  of  block  grants  for 

States  for  temporary  assistance  for  needy  fami-

