(C)  Any  other  provisions  the  Secretary  of 

Education  determines  are  necessary  to  protect 

the  interests  of  the  United  States  and  to  pro-

mote the purposes of this section. 

(2)  CLOSING INSTITUTION DEFINED.The 

term  closing  institution  means  an  institution  of 

higher education 

(A) that ceases to operate or plans to cease 

operations  before  all  enrolled  students  have 

completed their program of study; or 

(B)  that  has  an 

institutional 

location 

that 

(i)  provides  100  percent  of  at  least  1 

program  offered  by  the  institution  of  high-

er education; and 

(ii) ceases to operate or plans to cease 

operations before all enrolled students have 

completed their program of study. 

(3) TEACH-OUT PLANS. 

(A)  TEACH-OUT PLAN DEFINED.The 

term teach-out plan means a written plan de-

veloped by a closing institution that provides for 

the equitable treatment of students. 

