stitution  of  higher  education  that  meets 

the  requirements  of  section  101  or  section 

102(c)  of  the  Higher  Education  Act  of 

1965 (20 U.S.C. 1001; 1002(c)); 

(ii)  has  the  necessary  experience,  re-

sources, and support services to provide an 

educational  program  that  is  of  acceptable 

quality  and  reasonably  similar  in  content, 

delivery  modality,  and  scheduling  to  that 

provided  by  the  closing  institution  with 

