retary of Education shall publish standard language relat-

ing to closed school discharges for purposes of subsection 

(a)(5)(B)(v). 

(c) PROHIBITION ON MISREPRESENTATIONS. 

(1) IN GENERAL.An institution of higher edu-

cation  is  prohibited  from  engaging  in  misrepresenta-

tion  about  the  nature  of  teach-out  plans,  teach-out 

agreements, and transfer of credit. 

(2)  SANCTIONS.  Upon  determination,  after 

reasonable notice and opportunity for a hearing, that 

an  institution  of  higher  education  is  in  violation  of 

this subsection, the Secretary of Education 

(A)  shall  impose  a  civil  penalty  not  to  ex-

ceed $25,000 for each misrepresentation; and 

(B)  may  impose  an  additional  sanction  de-

scribed in section 497(c)(3) of the Higher Edu-

cation Act of 1965 (20 U.S.C. 1094(c)(3)). 

