(3)  DEFINITIONS.For  purposes  of  this  sub-

section: 

(A)  CERTIFICATION OF EMPLOYMENT. 

The  term  certification  of  employment,  used 

with  respect  to  a  borrower,  means  a  certifi-

cation  of  the  employment  of  the  borrower  in  a 

public  service 

job  (as  defined 

in  section 

455(m)(3)(B)  of  the  Higher  Education  Act  of 

1965) on or after October 1, 2007. 

(B)  COMPONENT LOAN.The  term  com-

ponent  loan,  used  with  respect  to  a  Federal 

Direct Consolidation Loan, means each loan for 

which  the  liability  has  been  discharged  by  the 

proceeds  of  the  Federal  Direct  Consolidation 

Loan, which 

(i)  may  include  a  loan  that  is  not  an 

eligible  Federal  Direct  Loan  (as  defined  in 

section  455(m)(3)(A)  of  the  Higher  Edu-

cation Act of 1965); and 

