(1)  POLICY.Each 

standard  promulgated 

under  this  section  shall  require  employers  to  adopt 

a  policy  prohibiting  the  discrimination  and  retalia-

tion  described  in  paragraph  (2)  by  any  person  (in-

cluding an agent of the employer). 

(2)  PROHIBITION.No  employer  (including  an 

agent of the employer) shall discriminate or retaliate 

against an employee for 

(A)  reporting  to  the  employer,  to  a  local, 

State,  or  Federal  government  agency,  or  to  the 

media or on a social media platform 

(i)  a  violation  of  a  standard  promul-

gated pursuant to this Act; 

(ii) a violation of an infectious disease 

exposure  control  plan  described  in  sub-

section (c)(1); or 

