SEC. 302. FLEXIBILITY FOR THE RUNAWAY AND HOMELESS 

YOUTH PROGRAM. 

During  the  public  health  emergency  declared  by  the 

Secretary  of  Health  and  Human  Services  under  section 

319  of  the  Public  Health  Service  Act  (42  U.S.C.  247d) 

on January 31, 2020, with respect to COVID19, and any 

renewal of such declaration, the Secretary may waive with 

respect  to  a  current  or  future  grantee  of  funds  provided 

to  carry  out  the  Runaway  and  Homeless  Youth  Act  (42 

U.S.C. 11201 et seq.) 

(1)  the  21-day  maximum  period  for  which  shel-

ter  may  be  provided  applicable  under  section 

311(a)(2)(B)(i) 

of 

such  Act 

(34  U.S.C. 

11211(a)(2)(B)(i)); 

(2)  the  20-youth  maximum  capacity  of  a  center 

or  facility  applicable  under  section  312(b)(2)(A)  of 

such Act (34 U.S.C. 11212(b)(2)(A)) if such grantee 

provides an assurance that waiving such requirement 

would  not  compromise  the  health  and  safety  of 

youth  or  staff  and  would  not  compromise  such 

grantees  ability  to  implement  the  applicable  guid-

ance  issued  by  the  Centers  for  Disease  Control  and 

Prevention to mitigate the spread of COVID19, in-

