SEC.  305.  CORPORATION  FOR  NATIONAL  AND  COMMUNITY 

SERVICE. 

(a) CNCS LEGISLATIVE FLEXIBILITIES. 

(1)  MATCH WAIVER.During  the  period  begin-

ning  on  the  date  of  the  enactment  of  this  Act  and 

ending on September 30, 2022, notwithstanding any 

other  provision  of  law,  if  a  grantee  of  the  Corpora-

tion  for  National  and  Community  Service  is  unable 

to  meet  a  requirement  to  provide  matching  funds 

due  to  funding  constraints  resulting  from  the 

COVID19  national  emergency,  the  Chief  Executive 

Officer of the Corporation for National and Commu-

nity Service may 

(A)  waive  any  requirement  that  such 

grantee  provide  matching  funds  for  a  program; 

and 

(B) increase the Federal share of the grant 

for such program up to 100 percent. 

(2)  END-OF-SERVICE CASH STIPEND.Section 

3514(a)(2)(B) of the CARES Act is amended by in-

serting  ,  or  the  full  value  of  the  stipend  under  sec-

tion  105(a)  of  title  I  of  the  Domestic  Volunteer 

