SEC.  208.  EXCLUSION  OF  CERTAIN  PUBLICLY  TRADED  AND 

FOREIGN ENTITIES. 

Section  7(a)(36)(D)  of  the  Small  Business  Act  (15 

U.S.C. 636(a)(36)(D)), as amended by section 204 is fur-

ther  amended  by  adding  at  the  end  the  following  new 

clause: 

(x)  EXCLUSION OF CERTAIN PUB-

LICLY TRADED AND FOREIGN ENTITIES. 

Effective  on  the  date  of  the  enactment  of 

this clause 

(I)  an  issuer,  the  securities  of 

which are traded on a national securi-

ties exchange, is not eligible to receive 

a  covered  loan  under  this  section;  and 

(II) an entity that is 51 percent 

or more owned by a foreign person, or 

the  management  and  daily  business 

operations  of  which  are  controlled  by 

a  foreign  person  (excluding  an  entity 

owned  and  controlled  by  a  person 

domiciled  in  a  territory  or  possession 

of the United States), is not eligible to 

receive  a  covered  loan  under  this  sec-

tion.. 

