crease  the  amount  of  the  covered  loan  to  the  max-

imum  amount  applicable,  subject  to  the  require-

ments of such section 7(a)(36). 

SEC. 218. TREATMENT OF CERTAIN CRIMINAL VIOLATIONS. 

(a)  IN GENERAL.Section  7(a)(36)  of  the  Small 

Business Act (15 U.S.C. 636(a)(36)), as amended by sec-

tion  101,  is  further  amended  by  adding  at  the  end  the 

following new subparagraph: 

(U)  TREATMENT OF CERTAIN CRIMINAL 

VIOLATIONS. 

(i)  FINANCIAL FRAUD OR DECEP-

TION.A  entity  that  is  a  business,  organi-

zation,  cooperative,  or  enterprise  may  not 

