(2)  CRITERIA.In  making  a  determination 

under  paragraph  (1),  the  Administrator  shall  con-

sider each of the following criteria: 

(A)  The  likelihood  that  the  applicant  will 

meet  the  goals  specified  in  the  business  plan  of 

the applicant. 

(B) The likelihood that the investments of 

the  applicant  will  directly  and  indirectly  create 

or preserve jobs. 

(C) The character and fitness of the man-

agement of the applicant. 

(D)  The  experience  and  background  of 

the management of the applicant. 

(E) The extent to which the applicant will 

concentrate  investment  activities  on  early-stage 

small businesses, growth-stage small businesses, 

scale-up small businesses, or covered small busi-

nesses, as applicable. 

(F)  The  likelihood  that  the  applicant  will 

achieve profitability. 

