Program participant 

(A)  for  initial  seed  investments,  during 

the  5-year  period  beginning  on  the  date  on 

which  the  Program  participant  first  accesses 

amounts from the account; and 

(B)  for  follow-on  investments  and  man-

agement  fees,  during  the  10-year  period  begin-

ning on the date on which the Program partici-

pant  first  accesses  amounts  from  the  account. 

(2) EXTENSION.Upon request by a Program 

participant,  the  Administrator  may  grant  a  1-year 

extension  of  the  period  described 

in  paragraph 

(1)(B) not more than 2 times. 

(3)  USE OF AMOUNTS.A  Program  partici-

pant  shall  invest  all  amounts  in  the  account  during 

the  10-year  period  beginning  on  the  date  on  which 

the Program participant first accesses amounts from 

the account. 

(d)  PRIORITY.The  Administrator  shall  prioritize 

making  seed  investments  under  this  section  to  Program 

participants in underlicensed States. 

(e) INVESTMENTS IN CERTAIN BUSINESSES. 

