SEC. 399G. DEFINITIONS. 

In this part: 

(1)  APPLICANT.The 

term 

applicant 

means 

(A) an incorporated body, a limited liabil-

ity  corporation,  or  a  limited  partnership  orga-

nized and chartered or otherwise existing under 

State  law  solely  for  the  purpose  of  performing 

the  functions  and  conducting  the  activities  con-

templated under this section; or 

(B)  a  bank-owned  applicant,  rural  busi-

ness  investment  company,  or  small  business  in-

vestment  company  licensed  under  section  301 

that  submits  an  application  to  operate  as  a 

micro-SBIC under section 399A. 

