(b)  CLERICAL AMENDMENT.The  table  of  sections 

for  chapter  77  of  the  Internal  Revenue  Code  of  1986  is 

amended by adding at the end the following new item: 

Sec. 7529. Application  of  earned  income  tax  credit  to  possessions  of  the 

United States.. 

SEC.  116.  TEMPORARY  SPECIAL  RULE  FOR  DETERMINING 

EARNED INCOME FOR PURPOSES OF EARNED 

INCOME TAX CREDIT. 

(a)  IN GENERAL.If  the  earned  income  of  the  tax-

payer  for  the  taxpayers  first  taxable  year  beginning  in 

2020  is  less  than  the  earned  income  of  the  taxpayer  for 

the  preceding  taxable  year,  the  credit  allowed  under  sec-

tion  32  of  the  Internal  Revenue  Code  of  1986  may,  at 

the  election  of  the  taxpayer,  be  determined  by  sub-

stituting- 

(1)  such  earned  income  for  the  preceding  tax-

able year, for 

(2)  such  earned  income  for  the  taxpayers  first 

taxable year beginning in 2020. 

(b) EARNED INCOME. 

(1) IN GENERAL.For purposes of this section, 

the  term  earned  income  has  the  meaning  given 

such  term  under  section  32(c)  of  the  Internal  Rev-

enue Code of 1986. 

(2)  APPLICATION TO JOINT RETURNS.For 

purposes  of  subsection  (a),  in  the  case  of  a  joint  re-

