(f) TREATMENT OF PLAN AMENDMENTS.For pur-

poses of this section 

(1)  if  two  or  more  plan  amendments  increas-

ing benefits or establishing new benefits are adopted 

in a plan year, such amendments shall be treated as 

a  single  amendment  adopted  on  the  last  day  of  the 

plan year; 

(2)  all  benefit  increases  and  new  benefits 

adopted in a single amendment are treated as a sin-

gle  benefit  increase,  irrespective  of  whether  the  in-

creases  and  new  benefits  take  effect  in  more  than 

one plan year; and 

(3)  increases  in  contributions  or  decreases  in 

plan  liabilities  which  are  scheduled  to  take  effect  in 

future  plan  years  may  be  taken  into  account  in  con-

nection  with  a  plan  amendment  if  they  have  been 

agreed  to  in  writing  or  otherwise  formalized  by  the 

date the plan amendment is adopted. 

