(b) RESTRICTIONS ON ACCEPTANCE BY COMPOSITE 

PLAN OF AGREEMENTS AND CONTRIBUTIONS. 

(1) IN GENERAL.The plan sponsor of a com-

posite  plan  shall  not  accept  or  recognize  a  collective 

bargaining  agreement  (or  any  modification  to  such 

agreement),  and  no  contributions  may  be  accepted 

and  no  benefits  may  be  accrued  or  otherwise  earned 

under the agreement 

(A) in any case in which the plan actuary 

of any defined benefit plan that would be treat-

