beginning on the date on which the employer entered 

into such collective bargaining agreement. 

(2)  NOTICE OF CESSATION OF OBLIGATION. 

Within 30 days of determining that an employer has 

ceased  to  have  an  obligation  to  contribute  to  a  leg-

acy  plan  with  respect  to  employees  employed  by  an 

employer  that  is  or  will  be  contributing  to  a  com-

posite plan with respect to service of such employees, 

the  plan  sponsor  of  the  legacy  plan  shall  notify  the 

plan sponsor of the composite plan of that cessation. 

(3)  NOTICE OF CESSATION OF ACCRUALS. 

Not  later  than  30  days  after  determining  that  an 

employer  has  ceased  to  have  an  obligation  to  con-

tribute  to  a  legacy  plan,  the  plan  sponsor  of  the 

composite  plan  shall  notify  the  bargaining  parties, 

the  active  participants  affected  by  the  cessation  of 

accruals,  the  Secretary,  the  Secretary  of  the  Treas-

ury,  and  the  Pension  Benefit  Guaranty  Corporation 

