(d) TRANSITION CONTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS. 

(1)  IN GENERAL.A  collective  bargaining 

agreement  satisfies  the  transition  contribution  re-

quirements of this subsection if the agreement 

(A)  authorizes  payment  of  contributions 

to  a  legacy  plan  at  a  rate  or  rates  equal  to  or 

greater than the transition contribution rate es-

tablished  by  the  legacy  plan  under  paragraph 

(2); and 

(B) does not provide for 

(i)  a  suspension  of  contributions  to 

the  legacy  plan  with  respect  to  any  period 

of service; or 

(ii)  any  new  direct  or  indirect  exclu-

sion  of  younger  or  newly  hired  employees 

of  the  employer  from  being  taken  into  ac-

count in determining contributions owed to 

the legacy plan. 

