(A)  IN GENERAL.The  transition  con-

tribution rate for a plan year is the contribution 

rate that, as certified by the actuary of the leg-

acy  plan  in  accordance  with  the  principles  in 

section  305(b)(3)(B),  is  reasonably  expected  to 

be adequate 

(i)  to  fund  the  normal  cost  for  the 

plan year; 

(ii)  to  amortize  the  plans  unfunded 

liabilities  in  level  annual  installments  over 

25  years,  beginning  with  the  plan  year  in 

which  the  transition  contribution  rate  is 

first established; and 

(iii)  to  amortize  any  subsequent 

changes  in  the  legacy  plans  unfunded  li-

ability  due  to  experience  gains  or  losses 

(including investment gains or losses, gains 

or  losses  due  to  contributions  greater  or 

less than the contributions made under the 

prior  transition  contribution  rate,  and 

other  actuarial  gains  or  losses),  changes  in 

actuarial  assumptions,  changes  to  the  leg-

acy  plans  benefits,  or  changes  in  funding 

method  over  a  period  of  15  plan  years  be-

