SEC.  806.  MERGERS  AND  ASSET  TRANSFERS  OF  COM-

POSITE PLANS. 

(a)  IN GENERAL.Assets  and  liabilities  of  a  com-

posite  plan  may  only  be  merged  with,  or  transferred  to, 

another plan if 

(1) the other plan is a composite plan; 

(2) the plan or plans resulting from the merg-

er or transfer is a composite plan; 

(3)  no  participants  accrued  benefit  or  adjust-

able  benefit  is  lower  immediately  after  the  trans-

action  than  it  was  immediately  before  the  trans-

action; and 

