(b) RESTRICTIONS ON ACCEPTANCE BY COMPOSITE 

PLAN OF AGREEMENTS AND CONTRIBUTIONS. 

(1) IN GENERAL.The plan sponsor of a com-

posite  plan  shall  not  accept  or  recognize  a  collective 

bargaining  agreement  (or  any  modification  to  such 

agreement),  and  no  contributions  may  be  accepted 

and  no  benefits  may  be  accrued  or  otherwise  earned 

under the agreement 

(A) in any case in which the plan actuary 

of any defined benefit plan that would be treat-

ed  as  a  legacy  plan  with  respect  to  such  com-

posite  plan  has 

certified  under 

section 

432(b)(3)  that  such  defined  benefit  plan  is  or 

will  be  in  critical  status  for  the  plan  year  in 

which  such  agreement  would  take  effect  or  for 

any of the succeeding 5 plan years, and 

(B)  unless  the  agreement  requires  each 

employer  who  is  a  party  to  such  agreement,  in-

cluding employers whose employees are not par-

ticipants in the legacy plan, to provide contribu-

tions  to  the  legacy  plan  with  respect  to  such 

