ductible  for  a  plan  year  shall  be  the  excess 

(if any) of 

(I)  160  percent  of  the  greater 

of 

(aa)  the  current  liability  of 

the  plan  determined  in  accord-

ance  with  the  principles  of  sec-

tion 431(c)(6)(D), or 

(bb)  the  present  value  of 

plan 

liabilities  as  determined 

under section 438, over 

(II) the fair market value of the 

plans  assets,  projected  to  the  end  of 

the plan year. 

