(2)  AMOUNTS SUBJECT TO LIABILITY AND RE-

COVERY.A  payment  described  in  this  paragraph  is 

a  payment  of  more  than  the  correct  amount  result-

ing from 

(A)  a  conviction  for  an  offense  under  sec-

tion 208(a), 811, or 1632(a) of the Social Secu-

rity Act; 

(B)  an  incorrect  or  incomplete  statement 

that  is  knowingly  made  and  material,  or  the 

knowing  concealment  of  material  information; 

or 

(C)  a  determination  that  a  representative 

payee  misused  benefits  made  under  section 

205(j),  807,  or  1631(a)(2)  of  the  Social  Secu-

rity Act, 

but only if such offense, misstatement, or misuse oc-

curred on or after March 1. 

