(3)  PERMISSIBLE USES AFTER THE EMER-

GENCY PERIOD.The  purpose  described 

in  this 

paragraph,  with  respect  to  a  State,  is  to  assist  eligi-

ble  individuals  who  had  to  relocate  to  a  nursing  fa-

cility  or  institutional  setting  from  their  homes  dur-

ing  the  COVID19  public  health  emergency  period 

in 

(A)  moving  back  to  their  homes  (including 

by  paying  for  moving  costs,  first  months  rent, 

and  other  one-time  expenses  and  start-up 

costs); 

(B)  resuming  home  and  community-based 

services; 

(C)  receiving  mental  health  services  and 

necessary  rehabilitative  service  to  regain  skills 

lost  while  relocated  during  the  public  health 

emergency period; and 

(D)  while  funds  attributable  to  the  in-

creased  FMAP  under  this  section  remain  avail-

able,  continuing  home  and  community-based 

services  for  eligible  individuals  who  were  served 

from  a  waiting  list  for  such  services  during  the 

public health emergency period. 

