TITLE IIMEDICARE 

PROVISIONS 

SEC.  201.  HOLDING  MEDICARE  BENEFICIARIES  HARMLESS 

FOR  SPECIFIED  COVID19  TREATMENT  SERV-

ICES  FURNISHED  UNDER  PART  A  OR  PART  B 

OF THE MEDICARE PROGRAM. 

(a) IN GENERAL.Notwithstanding any other provi-

sion  of  law,  in  the  case  of  a  specified  COVID19  treat-

ment service (as defined in subsection (b)) furnished dur-

ing any portion of the emergency period described in para-

graph (1)(B) of section 1135(g) of the Social Security Act 

(42 U.S.C. 1320b-5(g)) beginning on or after the date of 

the enactment of this Act to an individual entitled to bene-

