SEC.  202.  ENSURING  COMMUNICATIONS  ACCESSIBILITY 

FOR  RESIDENTS  OF  SKILLED  NURSING  FA-

CILITIES DURING THE COVID19 EMERGENCY 

PERIOD. 

(a)  IN GENERAL.Section  1819(c)(3)  of  the  Social 

Security Act (42 U.S.C. 1395i3(c)(3)) is amended 

(1)  in  subparagraph  (D),  by  striking  and  at 

the end; 

(2)  in  subparagraph  (E),  by  striking  the  period 

and inserting ; and; and 

(3) by adding at the end the following new sub-

paragraph: 

(F)  provide  for  reasonable  access  to  the 

use  of  a  telephone,  including  TTY  and  TDD 

services  (as  defined  for  purposes  of  section 

483.10  of  title  42,  Code  of  Federal  Regulations 

(or  a  successor  regulation)),  and  the  internet 

(to  the  extent  available  to  the  facility)  and  in-

form  each  such  resident  (or  a  representative  of 

such  resident)  of  such  access  and  any  changes 

in policies or procedures of such facility relating 

to limitations on external visitors.. 

