1135(g)(1)(B) of the Social Security Act. 

(3)  REASONABLE EVIDENCE OF UNEMPLOY-

MENT COMPENSATION.For  purposes  of  this  sub-

section, a taxpayer shall not be treated as having re-

ceived  (or  been  approved  to  receive)  unemployment 

compensation  for  any  week  unless  such  taxpayer 

provides documentation which demonstrates such re-

ceipt or approval. 

(4)  UNEMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION.For 

purposes of this subsection, the term unemployment 

compensation  has  the  meaning  given  such  term  in 

section  1311(c)(8)(E)  of  the  Patient  Protection  and 

Affordable Care Act.. 

