the  Indian  Self-Determination  and  Edu-

cation  Assistance  Act  (25  U.S.C.  5301  et 

seq.); or 

(ii)  receive  services  from  a  facility  op-

erated  by  the  Indian  Health  Services;  and 

(B) Tribal organizations and Urban Indian 

organizations. 
Subtitle ASupply Chain 

Improvements 

SEC. 511. MEDICAL SUPPLIES RESPONSE COORDINATOR. 

(a)  IN GENERAL.The  President  shall  appoint  a 

Medical  Supplies  Response  Coordinator  to  coordinate  the 

efforts  of  the  Federal  Government  regarding  the  supply 

and distribution of critical medical supplies and equipment 

related  to  detecting,  diagnosing,  preventing,  and  treating 

COVID19, including personal protective equipment, med-

ical devices, drugs, and vaccines. 

