Federal  Food,  Drug,  and  Cosmetic  Act  (21  U.S.C. 

360(j)(1)) is amended 

(1)  in  subparagraph  (D),  by  striking  and  at 

the end; 

(2)  in  subparagraph  (E),  by  striking  the  period 

at the end and inserting ; and; and 

(3) by adding at the end the following new sub-

paragraph: 

(F)  in  the  case  of  a  drug  contained  in  the  ap-

plicable list, a certification that the registrant has 

(i)  identified  every  other  establishment 

where manufacturing is performed for the drug; 

and 

(ii)  notified  each  known  foreign  establish-

ment  engaged  in  the  manufacture,  preparation, 

propagation,  compounding,  or  processing  of  the 

drug, including the active pharmaceutical ingre-

dient,  of  the  inclusion  of  the  drug  in  the  list 

and the obligation to register.. 

