SEC.  516.  RECOMMENDATIONS  TO  ENCOURAGE  DOMESTIC 

MANUFACTURING OF CRITICAL DRUGS. 

(a)  IN GENERAL.Not  later  than  14  days  after  the 

date  of  enactment  of  this  Act,  the  Secretary  shall  enter 

into  an  agreement  with  the  National  Academies  of 

Sciences,  Engineering,  and  Medicine  (referred  to  in  this 

section  as  the  National  Academies)  under  which,  not 

later  than  90  days  after  the  date  of  entering  into  the 

agreement, the National Academies will 

(1)  establish  a  committee  of  experts  who  are 

knowledgeable  about  drug  and  device  supply  issues, 

including 

(A)  sourcing  and  production  of  critical 

drugs and devices; 

(B)  sourcing  and  production  of  active 

pharmaceutical ingredients in critical drugs; 

(C)  the  raw  materials  and  other  compo-

nents for critical drugs and devices; and 

