process. 

(2)  CONTINUOUS

MANUFACTURING.The 

term continuous manufacturing 

(A)  means  a  process  where  the  input  ma-

terials  are  continuously  fed  into  and  trans-

formed  within  the  process,  and  the  processed 

output materials are continuously removed from 

the system; and 

(B) consists of an integrated process that 

consists  of  a  series  of  two  or  more  unit  oper-

ations. 

(3)  INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION. 

The  term  institution  of  higher  education  has  the 

meaning  given  such  term  in  section  101(a)  of  the 

Higher Education Act of 1965 (20 U.S.C. 1001(a)). 

(4)  SECRETARY.The  term  Secretary  means 

the Secretary of Health and Human Services, acting 

through the Commissioner of Food and Drugs.. 

