SEC.  535.  IMPROVED,  TRANSPARENT  PROCESSES  FOR  THE 

STRATEGIC NATIONAL STOCKPILE. 

(a)  IN GENERAL.Not  later  than  January  1,  2021, 

the  Secretary,  in  collaboration  with  the  Assistant  Sec-

retary  for  Preparedness  and  Response  and  the  Director 

of  the  Centers  for  Disease  Control  and  Prevention,  shall 

develop  and  implement  improved,  transparent  processes 

for  the  use  and  distribution  of  drugs,  vaccines  and  other 

biological  products,  medical  devices,  and  other  supplies 

(including  personal  protective  equipment,  ancillary  med-

ical supplies, and other applicable supplies required for the 

administration  of  drugs,  vaccines  and  other  biological 

products,  diagnostic  tests,  and  other  medical  devices  )  in 

the Strategic National Stockpile under section 319F2 of 

the  Public  Health  Service  Act  (42  U.S.C.  247d6b)  (in 

this section referred to as the Stockpile). 

(b)  PROCESSES.The  processes  developed  under 

subsection (a) shall include 

