interim final rule, or by guidance; and 

(2)  may  issue  such  regulations  or  guidance 

without  regard  to  the  procedures  otherwise  required 

by section 553 of title 5, United States Code. 

SEC. 547. GAO REPORT ON DIAGNOSTIC TESTS. 

(a)  GAO  STUDY.Not  later  than  18  months  after 

the date of enactment of this Act, the Comptroller General 

of  the  United  States  shall  submit  to  the  Committee  on 

Energy  and  Commerce  of  the  House  of  Representatives 

and the Committee on Health, Education, Labor and Pen-

sions  of  the  Senate  a  report  describing  the  response  of 

entities described in subsection (b) to the COVID19 pan-

demic with respect to the development, regulatory evalua-

tion, and deployment of diagnostic tests. 

(b)  ENTITIES DESCRIBED.Entities  described  in 

this subsection include 

(1)  laboratories,  including  public  health,  aca-

demic, clinical, and commercial laboratories; 

