ritories when deciding when to authorize labora-

tories to develop or perform diagnostic tests; 

(6) an assessment of the steps taken by labora-

tories  and  diagnostic  test  manufacturers  to  validate 

diagnostic  tests,  as  well  as  the  evidence  collected  by 

such entities to support validation; and 

(7) based on available reports, an assessment of 

the accuracy and sensitivity of a representative sam-

ple of available diagnostic tests. 

(d)  DEFINITION.In  this  section,  the  term  diag-

nostic  test  means  an  in  vitro  diagnostic  product  (as  de-

fined in section 809.3(a) of title 21, Code of Federal Regu-

lations) for 

(1) the detection of SARSCoV2; 

(2)  the  diagnosis  of  the  virus  that  causes 

COVID19; or 

