(f) MAINTENANCE OF EFFORT.The Secretary may 

award  a  grant  to  an  entity  under  subsection  (b)  only  if 

the  entity  demonstrates  to  the  satisfaction  of  the  Sec-

retary that 

(1) funds received through the grant will be ex-

pended  only  to  supplement,  and  not  supplant,  non- 

Federal and Federal funds otherwise available to the 

entity  for  the  purpose  of  addressing  core  public 

health infrastructure needs; and 

(2) with respect to activities for which the grant 

is  awarded,  the  entity  will  maintain  expenditures  of 

non-Federal  amounts  for  such  activities  at  a  level 

not  less  than  the  level  of  such  expenditures  main-

tained by the entity for the fiscal year preceding the 

fiscal year for which the entity receives the grant. 

