SEC.  551.  CORE  PUBLIC  HEALTH  INFRASTRUCTURE  AND 

ACTIVITIES FOR CDC. 

(a) IN GENERAL.The Secretary, acting through the 

Director  of  the  Centers  for  Disease  Control  and  Preven-

tion,  shall  expand  and  improve  the  core  public  health  in-

frastructure and activities of the Centers for Disease Con-

trol and Prevention to address unmet and emerging public 

health needs. 

(b) REPORT.The Secretary shall submit to the Con-

gress  an  annual  report  on  the  activities  funded  through 

this section. 

