(4)  PRESUMPTIVE CASE OF COVID19.For 

purposes  of  paragraph  (3)(B),  an  individual  shall  be 

presumed  to  have  COVID19  if  the  medical  record 

documentation of the individual supports a diagnosis 

of  COVID19,  even  if  the  individual  does  not  have 

a  positive  in  vitro  diagnostic  test  result  in  the  med-

ical record of the individual. 

(5) PENALTY.In the case of an eligible health 

care  provider  that  is  paid  a  reimbursement  under 

this section and that is in violation of paragraph (1) 

or  (2),  in  addition  to  any  other  penalties  that  may 

be prescribed by law, the Secretary may recoup from 

such  provider  up  to  the  full  amount  of  reimburse-

ment the provider receives under this section. 

