(1)  The  term  branch  campus  means  a  geo-

graphically  separate  site  at  least  100  miles  from  the 

main  campus  of  a  school  of  medicine  where  at  least 

one student completes at least 60 percent of the stu-

dents training leading to a degree of doctor of medi-

cine. 

