SEC. 701. DEFINITIONS. 

In this title: 

(1)  The  term  ancillary  medical  supplies  in-

cludes 

(A) vials; 

(B) bandages; 

(C) alcohol swabs; 

(D) syringes; 

(E) needles; 

(F)  gloves,  masks,  and  other  personal  pro-

tective equipment; 

(G) cold storage equipment; and 

(H)  other  products  the  Secretary  deter-

mines  necessary  for  the  administration  of  vac-

cines. 

(2)  The  term  Secretary  means  the  Secretary 

of Health and Human Services. 

