(e) EVALUATION.The Secretary shall 

(1) establish benchmarks and metrics to quan-

titatively  measure  and  evaluate  the  campaign  under 

this section; 

(2)  conduct  qualitative  assessments  regarding 

the campaign under this section; and 

(3)  prepare  and  submit  to  the  Committee  on 

Energy  and  Commerce  of  the  House  of  Representa-

tives  and  the  Committee  on  Health,  Education, 

Labor,  and  Pensions  of  the  Senate  an  evaluation  of 

the campaign under this section. 

(f)  SUPPLEMENT NOT SUPPLANT.Funds  made 

available to carry out this section shall be used to supple-

ment  and  not  supplant  other  Federal,  State,  local,  and 

Tribal public funds provided for activities described in this 

section. 

(g)  AUTHORIZATION OF APPROPRIATIONS.There 

is  authorized  to  be  appropriated  to  carry  out  this  section 

$200,000,000 for the period of fiscal years 2021 through 

2025.. 

