the emergency period (as defined in section 1135(g)(1) of 

the Social Security Act (42 U.S.C. 1320b-5(g)(1))) result-

ing from the COVID19 pandemic. 

SEC.  102.  PROHIBITION  ON  COPAYMENTS  AND  COST  SHAR-

ING  FOR  VETERANS  RECEIVING  PREVENTIVE 

SERVICES RELATING TO COVID19. 

(a)  PROHIBITION.The  Secretary  of  Veterans  Af-

fairs may not require any copayment or other cost sharing 

under  chapter  17  of  title  38,  United  States  Code,  for 

qualifying  coronavirus  preventive  services.  The  require-

ment  described  in  this  subsection  shall  take  effect  with 

respect  to  a  qualifying  coronavirus  preventive  service  on 

the specified date. 

(b) DEFINITIONS.In this section, the terms quali-

fying coronavirus preventive service and specified date 

have  the  meaning  given  those  terms  in  section  3203  of 

the CARES Act (Public Law 116136). 

