(5)  TRIBAL LAND.The  term  Tribal  land 

means 

(A) any land located within the boundaries 

of 

(i)  an  Indian  reservation,  pueblo,  or 

rancheria; or 

(ii)  a  former  reservation  within  Okla-

homa; 

(B) any land not located within the bound-

aries  of  an  Indian  reservation,  pueblo,  or 

rancheria, the title to which is held 

(i)  in  trust  by  the  United  States  for 

the  benefit  of  an  Indian  Tribe  or  an  indi-

vidual Indian; 

(ii)  by  an  Indian  Tribe  or  an  indi-

vidual Indian, subject to restriction against 

alienation under laws of the United States; 

or 

