(f)  ENFORCEMENT.A  violation  of  this  section  or  a 

regulation  promulgated  under  this  section,  including  the 

knowing  or  reckless  denial  of  an  internet  service  offering 

discounted by the emergency broadband benefit to an eligi-

ble  household  that  requests  such  an  offering,  shall  be 

treated as a violation of the Communications Act of 1934 

(47 U.S.C. 151 et seq.) or a regulation promulgated under 

such  Act.  The  Commission  shall  enforce  this  section  and 

the regulations promulgated under this section in the same 

manner,  by  the  same  means,  and  with  the  same  jurisdic-

tion, powers, and duties as though all applicable terms and 

provisions of the Communications Act of 1934 were incor-

porated into and made a part of this section. 

