(b) EXTENSION OF EMERGENCY PERIOD.An emer-

gency period may be extended within a State or any por-

tion  thereof  for  a  maximum  of  six  months,  if  the  State, 

or  in  the  case  of  Tribal  land,  a  Tribal  government,  pro-

vides written, public notice to the Commission stipulating 

that an extension is necessary in furtherance of the recov-

ery  related  to  COVID19.  The  Commission  shall,  within 

48  hours  after  receiving  such  notice,  post  the  notice  on 

the public website of the Commission. 

