(c)  EMERGENCY PERIODS DESCRIBED.An  emer-

gency  period  described  in  this  subsection  is  any  portion 

beginning  on  or  after  the  date  of  the  enactment  of  this 

section  of  the  duration  of  a  public  health  emergency  de-

clared pursuant to section 319 of the Public Health Serv-

ice Act (42 U.S.C. 247d) as a result of COVID19, includ-

ing any renewal thereof. 

