(II)  serving  a  sentence  for  a 

criminal conviction. 

(E)  CONFINEMENT FACILITY COMMU-

NICATIONS SERVICE.The  term  confinement 

facility communications service means a service 

that  allows  incarcerated  persons  to  make  elec-

tronic  communications 

(whether 

intrastate, 

