(3)  TRANSFER IN SATISFACTION OF ANTE-

CEDENT DEBT.A  transfer  of  livestock  subject  to  a 

dealer trust is not for value if the transfer is in sat-

isfaction of an antecedent debt or to a secured party 

pursuant to a security agreement. 

(f)  ENFORCEMENT.Whenever  the  Secretary  has 

reason  to  believe  that  a  dealer  subject  to  this  section  has 

failed  to  perform  the  duties  required  by  this  section  or 

whenever  the  Secretary  has  reason  to  believe  that  it  will 

be in the best interest of unpaid cash sellers, the Secretary 

shall do one or more of the following 

(1)  Appoint  an  independent  trustee  to  carry 

out  the  duties  required  by  this  section,  preserve 

trust assets, and enforce the trust. 

(2)  Serve  as  independent  trustee,  preserve 

trust assets, and enforce the trust. 

(3)  File  suit  in  the  United  States  district 

court  for  the  district  in  which  the  dealer  resides  to 

enjoin  the  dealers  failure  to  perform  the  duties  re-

quired  by  this  section,  preserve  trust  assets,  and  to 

enforce  the  trust.  Attorneys  employed  by  the  Sec-

retary  may,  with  the  approval  of  the  Attorney  Gen-

eral, represent the Secretary in any such suit. Noth-

