SEC. 304. SUPPORT FOR FARM STRESS PROGRAMS. 

(a)  IN GENERAL.The  Secretary  shall  make  grants 

to  State  departments  of  agriculture  (or  such  equivalent 

department)  to  expand  or  sustain  stress  assistance  pro-

grams for individuals who are engaged in farming, ranch-

ing, and other agriculture-related occupations, including 

(1)  programs  that  meet  the  criteria  specified  in 

section  7522(b)(1)  of  the  Food,  Conservation,  and 

Energy Act of 2008 (7 U.S.C. 5936(b)(1)); and 

(2)  any  State  initiatives  carried  out  as  of  the 

date of the enactment of this Act that provide stress 

assistance for such individuals. 

