SEC. 305. SUPPORT FOR PROCESSED COMMODITIES. 

(a)  RENEWABLE FUEL REIMBURSEMENT PRO-

GRAM. 

(1)  IN GENERAL.The  Secretary  shall  make 

payments in accordance with this subsection to eligi-

ble  entities  that  experienced  unexpected  market 

losses as a result of the COVID19 pandemic during 

the applicable period. 

(2) DEFINITIONS.In this section: 

(A)  APPLICABLE PERIOD.The  term  ap-

plicable  period  means  January  1,  2020, 

through May 1, 2020. 

(B) ELIGIBLE ENTITY.The term eligible 

entity  means  any  domestic  entity  or  facility 

that produced any qualified fuel in the calendar 

year 2019. 

(C)  QUALIFIED FUEL.The  term  quali-

fied fuel means any advanced biofuel, biomass- 

based  diesel,  cellulosic  biofuel,  conventional 

biofuel, or renewable fuel, as such terms are de-

fined  in  section  211(o)(1)  of  the  Clean  Air  Act 

(42 U.S.C. 7545(o)(1)), that is produced in the 

United States. 

(3) AMOUNT OF PAYMENT.The amount of the 

payment  payable  to  an  eligible  entity  shall  be  the 

sum of 

