hayed  or  grazed,  adequate  stubble  height  shall 

be  maintained  to  protect  the  soil  on  the  eligible 

land, as determined by the applicable State con-

servationist  after  considering  the  advice  of  the 

applicable State technical committee; and 

(B)  with  respect  to  eligible  land  that  is  so 

harvested for seed 

(i)  the  eligible  land  shall  not  be  eligi-

ble  to  be  insured  or  reinsured  under  the 

Federal  Crop  Insurance  Act  (7  U.S.C. 

1501 et seq.); and 

(ii)  the  annual  rental  rate  for  a  pay-

ment  under  a  contract  described  in  sub-

section (b) shall be $52.50 per acre. 

(d)  ACREAGE LIMITATION.Not  more 

than 

5,000,000  total  acres  of  eligible  land  may  be  enrolled 

under the pilot program under this section. 

(e)  FUNDING.There  is  appropriated,  out  of  any 

funds  in  the  Treasury  not  otherwise  appropriated,  such 

sums as may be necessary to carry out this section. 

