(1) RESPONSE TO IMMEDIATE NEEDS. 

(A)  IN GENERAL.Not  later  than  7  days 

after  the  date  of  the  enactment  of  this  Act,  the 

President,  in  coordination  with  the  National 

Response  Coordination  Center  of  the  Federal 

Emergency  Management  Agency,  the  Adminis-

trator of the Defense Logistics Agency, the Sec-

retary  of  Health  and  Human  Services,  the  Sec-

retary  of  Veterans  Affairs,  and  heads  of  other 

Federal  agencies  (as  appropriate),  shall  submit 

to  the  appropriate  congressional  committees  a 

report  assessing  the  immediate  needs  described 

in  subparagraph  (B)  to  combat  the  COVID19 

pandemic and the plan for meeting those imme-

diate needs. 

