(c)  DEFINITION OF AT RISK OF HOMELESSNESS. 

Notwithstanding  section  401(1)  of  the  McKinney-Vento 

Homeless  Assistance  Act  (42  U.S.C.  11360(1)),  for  pur-

poses  of  assistance  made  available  with  amounts  made 

available pursuant to subsection (b), the term at risk of 

homelessness  means,  with  respect  to  an  individual  or 

family, that the individual or family 

(1)  except  as  provided  in  subsection  (d)(1)(C), 

has  an  income  below  80  percent  of  the  median  in-

come  for  the  area  as  determined  by  the  Secretary; 

and 

(2)  has  an  inability  to  attain  or  maintain  hous-

ing  stability  or  has  insufficient  resources  to  pay  for 

rent or utilities. 

