(d) DEFINITIONS.For purposes of this Act, the fol-

lowing definitions shall apply: 

(1)  COVERED PERIOD.The  term  covered  pe-

riod  means,  with  respect  to  a  federally  backed 

mortgage  loan,  the  period  of  time  during  which  the 

borrower  under  such  loan  may  request  forbearance 

on  the  loan  under  section  4022(b)  of  the  CARES 

Act  (15  U.S.C.  9056;  Public  Law  116136;  134 

Stat. 490). 

(2)  COVID-19 

EMERGENCY.The 

term 

COVID19  emergency  has  the  meaning  given 

such  term  in  section  4022  of  the  CARES  Act  (15 

U.S.C.  9056;  Public  Law  116136;  134  Stat.  490). 

