the loan, based on the payment plan selected by 

the borrower or the borrowers loan status. 

(B)  LIMITATION ON PAYMENTS.The 

maximum  amount  of  aggregate  payments  that 

the  Secretary  of  the  Treasury  may  make  under 

subparagraph  (A)  with  respect  to  an  individual 

borrower is $10,000. 

(2)  NO CAPITALIZATION OF INTEREST.With 

respect  to  any  loan  in  repayment  until  February  1, 

2021,  interest  due  on  a  private  education  loan  dur-

ing  such  period  shall  not  be  capitalized  at  any  time 

until after February 1, 2021. 

