into  the  Fund  and  used  to  provide  financial  and 

technical  assistance  pursuant  to  section  108  of  the 

Riegle  Community  Development  and  Regulatory  Im-

provement  Act  of  1994  (12  U.S.C.  4707),  except 

that  subsection  (e)  of  that  section  shall  be  waived. 

(13)  EQUITY EQUIVALENT INVESTMENT OP-

TION. 

(A)  IN GENERAL.The  Secretary  shall 

establish  an  Equity  Equivalent  Investment  Op-

tion,  under  which,  with  respect  to  a  specific  in-

vestment  in  a  low-  and  moderate-income  com-

munity financial institution 

(i)  80  percent  of  such  investment  is 

made by the Secretary under the Program; 

and 

(ii)  20  percent  of  such  investment  if 

made by a banking institution. 

