for  the  providing  recipients  with  the  financial  coun-

seling  and  education  necessary  to  conduct  trans-

actions and manage their accounts. These loans pro-

vide  low-cost  alternatives  to  payday  loans  and  other 

nontraditional  forms  of  financing  that  often  impose 

excessive  interest  rates  and  fees  on  borrowers,  and 

lead  millions  of  Americans  to  fall  into  debt  traps. 

Small-dollar  loans  can  only  be  made  pursuant  to 

terms,  conditions,  and  practices  that  are  reasonable 

for the individual consumer obtaining the loan. 

(4)  Program  participation  is  restricted  to  eligi-

