(B)  MINORITY LENDING INSTITUTION. 

The term minority lending institution means a 

community development financial institution 

(i)  with  respect  to  which  a  majority 

of  the  total  number  of  loans  and  a  major-

ity  of  the  value  of  investments  of  the  com-

munity  development  financial  institution 

are  directed  at  minorities  and  other  tar-

geted populations; 

(ii)  that  is  a  minority  depository  in-

stitution,  as  defined  under  section  308  of 

the  Financial  Institutions  Reform,  Recov-

ery,  and  Enforcement  Act  of  1989  (12 

U.S.C. 1463 note), or otherwise considered 

to  be  a  minority  depository  institution  by 

the appropriate Federal banking agency; or 

(iii)  that  is  51  percent  owned  by  one 

or  more  socially  and  economically  dis-

advantaged individuals. 

(C)  ADDITIONAL DEFINITIONS.In  this 

paragraph,  the  terms  other  targeted  popu-

lations and socially and economically disadvan-

taged  individual  shall  have  the  meaning  given 

those terms by the Administrator.. 

