MAILED BALLOTS. 

(1)  IN GENERAL.A  State  may  not  refuse  to 

accept or process a ballot submitted by an individual 

by mail with respect to an election for Federal office 

in  the  State  on  the  grounds  that  the  individual  did 

not  meet  a  deadline  for  returning  the  ballot  to  the 

appropriate State or local election official if 

(A)  the  ballot  is  postmarked,  signed,  or 

otherwise  indicated  by  the  United  States  Postal 

