SEC. 324. RULES FOR COUNTING PROVISIONAL BALLOTS. 

(a)  STATEWIDE COUNTING OF PROVISIONAL BAL-

LOTS. 

(1)  IN GENERAL.For  purposes  of  section 

302(a)(4),  notwithstanding  the  precinct  or  polling 

place  at  which  a  provisional  ballot  is  cast  within  the 

State,  the  appropriate  election  official  shall  count 

each  vote  on  such  ballot  for  each  election  in  which 

the individual who cast such ballot is eligible to vote. 

(2)  EFFECTIVE DATE.This  subsection  shall 

apply with respect to the regularly scheduled general 

election  for  Federal  office  held  in  November  2020 

and each succeeding election for Federal office. 

(b)  UNIFORM AND NONDISCRIMINATORY STAND-

ARDS. 

(1)  IN GENERAL.Consistent  with  the  re-

quirements of section 302, each State shall establish 

uniform  and  nondiscriminatory  standards  for  the 

issuance,  handling,  and  counting  of  provisional  bal-

lots. 

(2)  EFFECTIVE DATE.This  subsection  shall 

apply with respect to the regularly scheduled general 

election  for  Federal  office  held  in  November  2020 

and each succeeding election for Federal office. 

