AGE.An absentee ballot obtained by a qualified in-

dividual  under  this  section  shall  be  considered  bal-

loting  materials  as  defined  in  section  107  for  pur-

poses  of  section  3406  of  title  39,  United  States 

Code. 

(5)  PROHIBITING REFUSAL TO ACCEPT BAL-

LOT FOR FAILURE TO MEET CERTAIN REQUIRE-

MENTS.A  State  shall  not  refuse  to  accept  and 

process  any  otherwise  valid  blank  absentee  ballot 

which  was  transmitted  to  a  qualified  individual 

under this section and used by the individual to vote 

in  the  election  solely  on  the  basis  of  the  following: 

(A)  Notarization  or  witness  signature  re-

quirements. 

