nuses,  awards  of  stock,  and  other  financial  benefits  pro-

vided  by  an  air  carrier  or  contractor  to  an  officer  or  em-

ployee of the air carrier or contractor. 

SEC. 108. MINIMUM AIR SERVICE GUARANTEES. 

(a)  IN GENERAL.The  Secretary  of  Transportation 

is authorized to require, to the extent reasonable and prac-

ticable,  an  air  carrier  provided  financial  assistance  under 

this title to maintain scheduled air transportation, as the 

Secretary  of  Transportation  determines  necessary,  to  en-

sure services to any point served by that air carrier before 

March  1,  2020,  continues  to  receive  a  basic  level  of  air 

service. 

