(d) REPORT.Not later than 30 days after the plan 

is developed under subsection (a), the Secretary shall sub-

mit to the appropriate committees of Congress such plan. 

(e)  DEFINITION OF AT-RISK EMPLOYEES.In  this 

section, the term at-risk employees means 

(1)  individuals  whose  job  duties  require  inter-

action  with  air  carrier  passengers  on  a  regular  and 

continuing basis that are employees of 

(A) air carriers; 

(B) air carrier contractors; 

(C) airports; and 

(D)  Federal  departments  or  agencies;  and 

(2)  air  traffic  controllers  and  systems  safety 

specialists of the Federal Aviation Administration. 

