(B)  UPDATED NOTICE WITH RESPECT TO 

THE SAME ITEM.If  an  owner  or  operator  is 

unable  to  acquire  an  item  described  in  a  notice 

submitted  under  subparagraph  (A)  by  the  date 

described  in  paragraph  (4)(B)(ii)  with  respect 

to the notice, the owner or operator may submit 

an updated notice with respect to that item. 

(2)  REASONABLE EFFORT DETERMINATION. 

With  respect  to  each  notice  submitted  under  para-

graph (1), the Secretary shall determine whether the 

owner  or  operator  submitting  the  notice  has  made 

reasonable  efforts  to  acquire  the  item  described  in 

the notice. 

(3) NOTICE OF COMPLIANCE.Not later than 7 

days  after  the  date  on  which  an  owner  or  operator 

acquires  an  item  described  in  a  notice  submitted  by 

that  owner  or  operator  under  paragraph  (1)  in  a 

quantity  sufficient  to  comply  with  the  requirements 

prescribed  under  subsection  (b)(1),  the  owner  or  op-

erator  shall  submit  to  the  Secretary  a  written  notice 

of compliance with those requirements. 

