SEC. 103. INSPECTOR GENERAL INDEPENDENCE. 

(a) SHORT TITLE.This section may be cited as the 

Inspector General Independence Act. 

(b)  AMENDMENT.The  Inspector  General  Act  of 

1978 (5 U.S.C. App.) is amended 

(1) in section 3(b) 

(A)  by  striking  An  Inspector  General 

and inserting (1) An Inspector General; 

(B)  by  inserting  after  by  the  President 

the  following:  in  accordance  with  paragraph 

(2); and 

(C)  by  inserting  at  the  end  the  following 

new paragraph: 

(2)  The  President  may  remove  an  Inspector 

General only for any of the following grounds: 

(A) Permanent incapacity. 

(B) Inefficiency. 

(C) Neglect of duty. 

(D) Malfeasance. 

(E)  Conviction  of  a  felony  or  conduct  in-

volving moral turpitude. 

