TITLE IIIFEDERAL 

WORKFORCE 

SEC.  301.  COVID19  TELEWORKING  REQUIREMENTS  FOR 

FEDERAL EMPLOYEES. 

(a) MANDATED TELEWORK. 

(1)  IN GENERAL.Effective  immediately  upon 

the  date  of  enactment  of  this  Act,  the  head  of  any 

Federal  agency  shall  require  any  employee  of  such 

agency  who  is  authorized  to  telework  under  chapter 

65 of title 5, United States Code, or any other provi-

sion  of  law  to  telework  during  the  period  beginning 

on  the  date  of  enactment  of  this  Act  and  ending  on 

December 31, 2020. 

(2) DEFINITIONS.In this subsection 

(A) the term employee means 

(i) an employee of the Library of Con-

gress; 

(ii)  an  employee  of  the  Government 

Accountability Office; 

(iii)  a  covered  employee  as  defined  in 

section  101  of  the  Congressional  Account-

ability  Act  of  1995  (2  U.S.C.  1301),  other 

than an applicant for employment; 

