(b)  REQUIRING ISSUANCE TO BE COMPETITIVE 

WITH OTHER FORMS OF BORROWING.The Council may 

authorize the issuance of bonds, notes, or other obligations 

under  subsection  (a)  only  if  the  issuance  of  such  bonds, 

notes,  and  other  obligations  is  competitive  with  other 

forms of borrowing in the financial market. 

(c)  TREATMENT AS GENERAL OBLIGATION.Any 

bond, note, or other obligation issued under subsection (a) 

shall,  if  provided  in  the  act  of  the  Council,  be  a  general 

obligation of the District. 

(d) PAYMENTS NOT SUBJECT TO APPROPRIATION. 

