SEC.  603.  UNITED  STATES  POSTAL  SERVICE  BORROWING 

AUTHORITY. 

Subsection (b)(2) of section 6001 of the Coronavirus 

Aid, Relief, and Economic Security Act (Public Law 116 

136) is amended to read as follows: 

(2) the Secretary of the Treasury shall lend up 

to  the  amount  described  in  paragraph  (1)  at  the  re-

quest  of  the  Postal  Service  subject  to  the  terms  and 

conditions  of  the  note  purchase  agreement  between 

the  Postal  Service  and  the  Federal  Financing  Bank 

in effect on September 29, 2018.. 

