authorization  or  deferred  action,  or  register  with,  or 

pay  a  fee  to,  the  Secretary  of  Homeland  Security  or 

the head of any other Federal agency; or 

(2)  to  appear  before  an  agent  of  the  Depart-

ment  of  Homeland  Security  or  any  other  Federal 

agency  for  an  interview,  examination,  or  any  other 

purpose. 

(d)  ALIENS DESCRIBED.An  alien  is  described  in 

this subsection if the alien 

(1)  on  the  date  of  the  enactment  of  this  title 

(A)  is  physically  present  in  the  United 

States; and 

(B)  is  inadmissible  to,  or  deportable  from, 

the United States; and 

(2)  engaged  in  essential  critical  infrastructure 

labor  or  services  in  the  United  States  prior  to  the 

period  described  in  subsection  (e)  and  continues  to 

engage  in  such  labor  or  services  during  such  period. 

(e)  PERIOD DESCRIBED.The  period  described  in 

this subsection 

(1)  begins  on  the  first  day  of  the  public  health 

emergency  declared  by  the  Secretary  of  Health  and 

Human  Services  under  section  319  of  the  Public 

