ice  requirements  for  a  waiver  under  such  sec-

tion  on  or  before  the  date  of  the  enactment  of 

this title; and 

(B)  provides  a  statement  to  the  Secretary 

of Homeland Security attesting that the alien is 

engaged  in  or  will  engage  in  the  practice  of 

medicine or medical research involving the diag-

nosis, treatment, or prevention of COVID19. 

(3)  PERIOD DESCRIBED.The  period  described 

in this paragraph is the period beginning on the date 

of  the  enactment  of  this  title  and  ending  180  days 

after the termination of the public health emergency 

declared  by  the  Secretary  of  Health  and  Human 

Services  under  section  319  of  the  Public  Health 

Service  Act  (42  U.S.C.  247d),  with  respect  to 

COVID19. 

