(3)  NATIONAL EMERGENCY RELATING TO A 

COMMUNICABLE DISEASE.The 

term 

national 

emergency  relating  to  a  communicable  disease 

means 

(A)  an  emergency  involving  Federal  pri-

mary  responsibility  determined  to  exist  by  the 

President  under  the  section  501(b)  of  the  Rob-

ert  T.  Stafford  Disaster  Relief  and  Emergency 

Assistance  Act  (42  U.S.C.  5191(b))  with  re-

spect to a communicable disease; or 

(B)  a  national  emergency  declared  by  the 

President  under  the  National  Emergencies  Act 

(50 U.S.C. 1601 et seq.) with respect to a com-

municable disease. 

