(e)  LIMITATION ON SUPERVISED RELEASE.Begin-

ning  on  the  date  on  which  a  national  emergency  relating 

to  a  communicable  disease  is  declared  and  ending  on  the 

date that is 60 days after such national emergency expires, 

the  Office  of  Probation  and  Pretrial  Services  of  the  Ad-

ministrative Office of the United States Courts shall take 

measures  to  prevent  the  spread  of  the  communicable  dis-

ease among individuals under supervision by 

(1) suspending the requirement that individuals 

determined  to  be  a  lower  risk  of  reoffending,  or  any 

other  individuals  determined  to  be  appropriate  by 

the supervising probation officer, report in person to 

their probation or parole officer; 

(2) identifying individuals who have successfully 

completed  not  less  than  18  months  of  supervision 

and  transferring  such  individuals  to  administrative 

supervision  or  petitioning  the  court  to  terminate  su-

pervision, as appropriate; and 

