which  shall  be  equal  to  the  period  of  time 

remaining  on  the  term  of  probation  origi-

nally  imposed  at  the  time  the  defendant 

was most recently placed in custody, unless 

the  court  determines  that  decreasing  the 

length  of  the  term  of  probation  is  in  the 

interest of justice. 

(ii)  In  the  case  of  a  revoked  term  of 

supervised  release,  the  court  shall  continue 

the  defendant  on  supervised  release,  the 

duration  of  which  shall  be  equal  to  the  pe-

riod  of  time  the  defendant  had  remaining 

on  supervised  release  when  the  defendant 

was most recently placed in custody, unless 

the  court  determines  that  decreasing  the 

