SEC.  206.  EFFECTIVE  ASSISTANCE  OF  COUNSEL  IN  THE 

DIGITAL ERA ACT. 

(a)  PROHIBITION ON MONITORING.Not  later  than 

180 days after the date of the enactment of this title, the 

Attorney  General  shall  create  a  program  or  system,  or 

modify  any  program  or  system  that  exists  on  the  date  of 

enactment of this title, through which an incarcerated per-

son  sends  or  receives  an  electronic  communication,  to  ex-

clude from monitoring the contents of any privileged elec-

tronic communication. In the case that the Attorney Gen-

eral  creates  a  program  or  system  in  accordance  with  this 

subsection, the Attorney General shall, upon implementing 

such  system,  discontinue  using  any  program  or  system 

that  exists  on  the  date  of  enactment  of  this  title  through 

which an incarcerated person sends or receives a privileged 

