with  an  attorney  who  is  participating 

in such a legal proceeding. 

(3)  MOTION TO SUPPRESS.In  a  case  in  which 

retained  contents  have  been  accessed  in  violation  of 

this  subsection,  a  court  may  suppress  evidence  ob-

tained  or  derived  from  access  to  such  contents  upon 

motion of the defendant. 

