SEC. 208. MORATORIUM ON FEES AND FINES. 

(a) IN GENERAL.During the covered emergency pe-

riod, and for fiscal years 2020, 2021, and 2022, the Attor-

ney General is authorized make grants to State and local 

courts that comply with the requirement under subsection 

(b) to ensure that such recipients are able to continue op-

erations. 

(b) REQUIREMENT TO IMPOSE MORATORIUM ON IM-

POSITION AND COLLECTION OF FEES AND FINES.To be 

eligible for a grant under this section, a court shall imple-

ment  a  moratorium  on  the  imposition  and  collection  (in-

cluding  by  a  unit  of  local  government  or  a  State)  of  fees 

and fines imposed by that court 

(1) not later than 120 day after the date of the 

enactment of this section; 

