SEC. 210. SEVERABILITY. 

If any provision of this title or any amendment made 

by  this  title,  or  the  application  of  a  provision  or  amend-

ment to any person or circumstance, is held to be invalid, 

the  remainder  of  this  title  and  the  amendments  made  by 

this title, and the application of the provisions and amend-

ments  to  any  other  person  not  similarly  situated  or  to 

other circumstances, shall not be affected by the holding. 

