SEC.  406.  INFORMATION  COLLECTION  BY  STATES  AND 

UNITS OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT. 

(a) DEFINITIONS.In this section: 

(1)  APPLICABLE AGENCY.The  term  applica-

ble  agency,  with  respect  to  an  eligible  entity  that 

is 

(A) a State, means 

(i)  a  law  enforcement  agency  of  the 

State; and 

(ii)  a  law  enforcement  agency  of  a 

unit  of  local  government  within  the  State 

that 

(I) is a priority agency; and 

(II)  receives  a  subgrant  from  the 

State under this section; and 

(B)  a  unit  of  local  government,  means  a 

law enforcement agency of the unit of local gov-

ernment that is a priority agency. 

(2)  COVERED AGENCY.The  term 

covered 

agency means 

(A) a State law enforcement agency; or 

(B) a priority agency. 

